                            <comment id="16582055" author="rupsshankar" created="Thu, 16 Aug 2018 07:00:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This test was failing intermittently because it was checking the tlog file sizes on disk after hard commits were automatically triggered. This was problematic because a triggered hard commit gets scheduled for some point (soon) in the future, so the check was not always guaranteed to succeed. Have changed this to check the current tlog object&apos;s stream size directly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16583092" author="anshumg" created="Thu, 16 Aug 2018 21:43:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Rupa. I&apos;ve updated the patch to fix a failing precommit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, for everyone else - I work with Rupa and we beasted the test 700 times and this didn&apos;t fail at all after the fix. I&apos;ll commit this now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
